  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "- [David] Good day, good wordsmiths."
      },
      {
        "start": 1.9,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "We have a fearsome foursome\nof words for you today"
      },
      {
        "start": 4.5,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "in the Vocabulary Corner."
      },
      {
        "start": 6.4,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "You know the drill, definitions,"
      },
      {
        "start": 8.1,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "and then if conditions permit,"
      },
      {
        "start": 9.3,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "we'll use each word in a sentence."
      },
      {
        "start": 11.7,
        "duration": 3.7,
        "text": "The words for this video\nare critical, approximately,"
      },
      {
        "start": 15.4,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "moreover, and conversely."
      },
      {
        "start": 17.6,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "Critical is an adjective that\ncan mean two different things:"
      },
      {
        "start": 20.8,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "very important, and also\npointing out faults or flaws."
      },
      {
        "start": 25.4,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "So water, right, is\ncritical for human survival."
      },
      {
        "start": 28.8,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "I need to drink water to live.\nThat's one kind of critical."
      },
      {
        "start": 32.0,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "But my friend, Gingabeeb the Judgmental..."
      },
      {
        "start": 35.2,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "- [Gingabeeb] Your\nglasses are smudged today."
      },
      {
        "start": 37.4,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "- [David] Can be the\nother kind of critical"
      },
      {
        "start": 40.5,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "and point out all my\nfailings as she sees them."
      },
      {
        "start": 43.1,
        "duration": 0.9,
        "text": "Hi, Gingabeeb."
      },
      {
        "start": 44.1,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "- [Gingabeeb] Hi. I don't\nlike that shirt on you."
      },
      {
        "start": 46.1,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "- [David] I'm just gonna keep going."
      },
      {
        "start": 47.3,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "- [Gingabeeb] Rude."
      },
      {
        "start": 48.1,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "- [David] Approximately is an adverb"
      },
      {
        "start": 49.9,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "that means around or close to."
      },
      {
        "start": 52.1,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "So in approximately 10 minutes,"
      },
      {
        "start": 54.6,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "Gingabeeb will get tired of doing this"
      },
      {
        "start": 56.3,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "and go back to her little burrow."
      },
      {
        "start": 58.0,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "- [Gingabeeb] It's not\na burrow, it's a barrow."
      },
      {
        "start": 60.9,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "- [David] Moreover is an adverb"
      },
      {
        "start": 62.5,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "that means also or in addition."
      },
      {
        "start": 65.4,
        "duration": 4.1,
        "text": "And conversely, one last\nadverb, means on the other hand."
      },
      {
        "start": 69.5,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "- [Gingabeeb] You left\nout in an opposite way."
      },
      {
        "start": 71.8,
        "duration": 4.1,
        "text": "- [David] Yes, fine, it also\nmeans in an opposite way."
      },
      {
        "start": 75.9,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "Thank you, Gingabeeb the judgmental."
      },
      {
        "start": 78.6,
        "duration": 1.0,
        "text": "- [Gingabeeb] You are not very good"
      },
      {
        "start": 79.7,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "at disguising your irritation."
      },
      {
        "start": 81.7,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "- [David] Let's break\nthese words down, shall we?"
      },
      {
        "start": 84.3,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "Crit in critical comes from a Greek root,"
      },
      {
        "start": 87.3,
